  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba  \u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0d89\u0dc4\u0dc5\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Train fares go up",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Cabinet approval has been granted to revise the railway fares.",
        "Accordingly, approval has been granted to revise the passenger fares which have not been revised for more than five years and the freight, postal and other charges which have not been revised for a period of 14 years.",
        "The proposal made by Hon. Bandula Gunawardena, Minister of Transport and Highways, to proceed with the relevant activities, was approved.",
        "The proposal made by the Minister states that although the Sri Lanka Railway Department has adopted a concessionary fare system in line with government policy, this decision has to be taken to avoid losses incurred by the Department due to the recent sharp rise in fuel prices."
      ],
